{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1617,"text":"So when I was eight years old,"},{"time":3582,"text":"a new girl came to join the class,"},{"time":5740,"text":"and she was so impressive,"},{"time":8773,"text":"as the new girl always seems to be."},{"time":11055,"text":"She had vast quantities of very shiny hair"},{"time":13733,"text":"and a cute little pencil case,"},{"time":16773,"text":"super strong on state capitals,"},{"time":20361,"text":"just a great speller."},{"time":22853,"text":"And I just curdled with jealousy that year,"},{"time":27803,"text":"until I hatched my devious plan."},{"time":31346,"text":"So one day I stayed a little late after school,"},{"time":35579,"text":"a little too late, and I lurked in the girls' bathroom."},{"time":39659,"text":"When the coast was clear, I emerged,"},{"time":41994,"text":"crept into the classroom,"},{"time":43733,"text":"and took from my teacher's desk the grade book."},{"time":47590,"text":"And then I did it."},{"time":49926,"text":"I fiddled with my rival's grades,"},{"time":52293,"text":"just a little, just demoted some of those A's."},{"time":55123,"text":"All of those A's. (Laughter)"},{"time":58222,"text":"And I got ready to return the book to the drawer,"},{"time":61965,"text":"when hang on, some of my other classmates"},{"time":64999,"text":"had appallingly good grades too."},{"time":68492,"text":"So, in a frenzy,"},{"time":70540,"text":"I corrected everybody's marks,"},{"time":72528,"text":"not imaginatively."},{"time":74437,"text":"I gave everybody a row of D's"},{"time":76951,"text":"and I gave myself a row of A's,"},{"time":79752,"text":"just because I was there, you know, might as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82552,"text":"And I am still baffled by my behavior."},{"time":88162,"text":"I don't understand where the idea came from."},{"time":90574,"text":"I don't understand why I felt so great doing it."},{"time":93903,"text":"I felt great."},{"time":95426,"text":"I don't understand why I was never caught."},{"time":98005,"text":"I mean, it should have been so blatantly obvious."},{"time":99601,"text":"I was never caught."},{"time":100914,"text":"But most of all, I am baffled by,"},{"time":103435,"text":"why did it bother me so much"},{"time":104942,"text":"that this little girl, this tiny little girl,"},{"time":106886,"text":"was so good at spelling?"},{"time":108600,"text":"Jealousy baffles me."},{"time":110710,"text":"It's so mysterious, and it's so pervasive."},{"time":113634,"text":"We know babies suffer from jealousy."},{"time":116100,"text":"We know primates do. Bluebirds are actually very prone."},{"time":119750,"text":"We know that jealousy is the number one cause"},{"time":123270,"text":"of spousal murder in the United States."},{"time":126186,"text":"And yet, I have never read a study"},{"time":129290,"text":"that can parse to me its loneliness"},{"time":132205,"text":"or its longevity or its grim thrill."},{"time":137059,"text":"For that, we have to go to fiction,"},{"time":139906,"text":"because the novel is the lab"},{"time":142246,"text":"that has studied jealousy"},{"time":143820,"text":"in every possible configuration."},{"time":145894,"text":"In fact, I don't know if it's an exaggeration to say"},{"time":149218,"text":"that if we didn't have jealousy,"},{"time":151250,"text":"would we even have literature?"},{"time":153800,"text":"Well no faithless Helen, no \"Odyssey.\""},{"time":157390,"text":"No jealous king, no \"Arabian Nights.\""},{"time":160228,"text":"No Shakespeare."},{"time":163365,"text":"There goes high school reading lists,"},{"time":165555,"text":"because we're losing \"Sound and the Fury,\""},{"time":167367,"text":"we're losing \"Gatsby,\" \"Sun Also Rises,\""},{"time":169616,"text":"we're losing \"Madame Bovary,\" \"Anna K.\""},{"time":173743,"text":"No jealousy, no Proust. And now, I mean,"},{"time":176150,"text":"I know it's fashionable to say that Proust"},{"time":177911,"text":"has the answers to everything,"},{"time":179518,"text":"but in the case of jealousy,"},{"time":182224,"text":"he kind of does."},{"time":184965,"text":"This year is the centennial of his masterpiece, \"In Search of Lost Time,\""},{"time":188951,"text":"and it's the most exhaustive study of sexual jealousy"},{"time":192952,"text":"and just regular competitiveness, my brand,"},{"time":195104,"text":"that we can hope to have. (Laughter)"},{"time":197689,"text":"And we think about Proust, we think"},{"time":200116,"text":"about the sentimental bits, right?"},{"time":201610,"text":"We think about a little boy trying to get to sleep."},{"time":203565,"text":"We think about a madeleine moistened in lavender tea."},{"time":207746,"text":"We forget how harsh his vision was."},{"time":209772,"text":"We forget how pitiless he is."},{"time":211612,"text":"I mean, these are books that Virginia Woolf said"},{"time":213933,"text":"were tough as cat gut."},{"time":216269,"text":"I don't know what cat gut is,"},{"time":218317,"text":"but let's assume it's formidable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221218,"text":"Let's look at why they go so well together,"},{"time":224436,"text":"the novel and jealousy, jealousy and Proust."},{"time":228114,"text":"Is it something as obvious as that jealousy,"},{"time":231345,"text":"which boils down into person, desire, impediment,"},{"time":234728,"text":"is such a solid narrative foundation?"},{"time":239396,"text":"I don't know. I think it cuts very close to the bone,"},{"time":242071,"text":"because let's think about what happens"},{"time":244120,"text":"when we feel jealous."},{"time":245898,"text":"When we feel jealous, we tell ourselves a story."},{"time":249850,"text":"We tell ourselves a story about other people's lives,"},{"time":254133,"text":"and these stories make us feel terrible"},{"time":256807,"text":"because they're designed to make us feel terrible."},{"time":259030,"text":"As the teller of the tale and the audience,"},{"time":261564,"text":"we know just what details to include,"},{"time":263538,"text":"to dig that knife in. Right?"},{"time":267107,"text":"Jealousy makes us all amateur novelists,"},{"time":270462,"text":"and this is something Proust understood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272478,"text":"In the first volume, Swann's Way,"},{"time":275651,"text":"the series of books,"},{"time":277475,"text":"Swann, one of the main characters,"},{"time":279181,"text":"is thinking very fondly of his mistress"},{"time":282409,"text":"and how great she is in bed,"},{"time":284101,"text":"and suddenly, in the course of a few sentences,"},{"time":287143,"text":"and these are Proustian sentences,"},{"time":289184,"text":"so they're long as rivers,"},{"time":290696,"text":"but in the course of a few sentences,"},{"time":292959,"text":"he suddenly recoils and he realizes,"},{"time":295366,"text":"\"Hang on, everything I love about this woman,"},{"time":298649,"text":"somebody else would love about this woman."},{"time":302420,"text":"Everything that she does that gives me pleasure"},{"time":305511,"text":"could be giving somebody else pleasure,"},{"time":307220,"text":"maybe right about now.\""},{"time":309498,"text":"And this is the story he starts to tell himself,"},{"time":312282,"text":"and from then on, Proust writes that"},{"time":314145,"text":"every fresh charm Swann detects in his mistress,"},{"time":317192,"text":"he adds to his \"collection of instruments"},{"time":319856,"text":"in his private torture chamber.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":323478,"text":"Now Swann and Proust, we have to admit,"},{"time":325753,"text":"were notoriously jealous."},{"time":327429,"text":"You know, Proust's boyfriends would have to leave"},{"time":329133,"text":"the country if they wanted to break up with him."},{"time":331737,"text":"But you don't have to be that jealous"},{"time":334640,"text":"to concede that it's hard work. Right?"},{"time":337551,"text":"Jealousy is exhausting."},{"time":339160,"text":"It's a hungry emotion. It must be fed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342807,"text":"And what does jealousy like?"},{"time":344896,"text":"Jealousy likes information."},{"time":347986,"text":"Jealousy likes details."},{"time":350375,"text":"Jealousy likes the vast quantities of shiny hair,"},{"time":353198,"text":"the cute little pencil case."},{"time":355664,"text":"Jealousy likes photos."},{"time":357206,"text":"That's why Instagram is such a hit. (Laughter)"},{"time":360936,"text":"Proust actually links the language of scholarship and jealousy."},{"time":364897,"text":"When Swann is in his jealous throes,"},{"time":367339,"text":"and suddenly he's listening at doorways"},{"time":369510,"text":"and bribing his mistress' servants,"},{"time":371533,"text":"he defends these behaviors."},{"time":372985,"text":"He says, \"You know, look, I know you think this is repugnant,"},{"time":375402,"text":"but it is no different"},{"time":377208,"text":"from interpreting an ancient text"},{"time":379558,"text":"or looking at a monument.\""},{"time":381225,"text":"He says, \"They are scientific investigations"},{"time":383822,"text":"with real intellectual value.\""},{"time":386825,"text":"Proust is trying to show us that jealousy"},{"time":388937,"text":"feels intolerable and makes us look absurd,"},{"time":391828,"text":"but it is, at its crux, a quest for knowledge,"},{"time":396498,"text":"a quest for truth, painful truth,"},{"time":399899,"text":"and actually, where Proust is concerned,"},{"time":401828,"text":"the more painful the truth, the better."},{"time":404620,"text":"Grief, humiliation, loss:"},{"time":409357,"text":"These were the avenues to wisdom for Proust."},{"time":412313,"text":"He says, \"A woman whom we need,"},{"time":416215,"text":"who makes us suffer, elicits from us"},{"time":419001,"text":"a gamut of feelings far more profound and vital"},{"time":422506,"text":"than a man of genius who interests us.\""},{"time":426945,"text":"Is he telling us to just go and find cruel women?"},{"time":429820,"text":"No. I think he's trying to say"},{"time":432117,"text":"that jealousy reveals us to ourselves."},{"time":435286,"text":"And does any other emotion crack us open"},{"time":438182,"text":"in this particular way?"},{"time":440510,"text":"Does any other emotion reveal to us"},{"time":442590,"text":"our aggression and our hideous ambition"},{"time":445923,"text":"and our entitlement?"},{"time":448322,"text":"Does any other emotion teach us to look"},{"time":450972,"text":"with such peculiar intensity?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":454164,"text":"Freud would write about this later."},{"time":456316,"text":"One day, Freud was visited"},{"time":458570,"text":"by this very anxious young man who was consumed"},{"time":460892,"text":"with the thought of his wife cheating on him."},{"time":463395,"text":"And Freud says, it's something strange about this guy,"},{"time":465472,"text":"because he's not looking at what his wife is doing."},{"time":467586,"text":"Because she's blameless; everybody knows it."},{"time":469557,"text":"The poor creature is just"},{"time":470887,"text":"under suspicion for no cause."},{"time":472885,"text":"But he's looking for things that his wife is doing"},{"time":475694,"text":"without noticing, unintentional behaviors."},{"time":478194,"text":"Is she smiling too brightly here,"},{"time":480511,"text":"or did she accidentally brush up against a man there?"},{"time":483851,"text":"[Freud] says that the man is becoming"},{"time":486527,"text":"the custodian of his wife's unconscious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490875,"text":"The novel is very good on this point."},{"time":492696,"text":"The novel is very good at describing how jealousy"},{"time":495504,"text":"trains us to look with intensity but not accuracy."},{"time":499488,"text":"In fact, the more intensely jealous we are,"},{"time":503563,"text":"the more we become residents of fantasy."},{"time":506082,"text":"And this is why, I think, jealousy doesn't"},{"time":509002,"text":"just provoke us to do violent things"},{"time":511818,"text":"or illegal things."},{"time":513818,"text":"Jealousy prompts us to behave in ways"},{"time":516100,"text":"that are wildly inventive."},{"time":518458,"text":"Now I'm thinking of myself at eight, I concede,"},{"time":520901,"text":"but I'm also thinking of this story I heard on the news."},{"time":524920,"text":"A 52-year-old Michigan woman was caught"},{"time":528828,"text":"creating a fake Facebook account"},{"time":531697,"text":"from which she sent vile, hideous messages"},{"time":535420,"text":"to herself for a year."},{"time":539645,"text":"For a year. A year."},{"time":541770,"text":"And she was trying to frame"},{"time":543645,"text":"her ex-boyfriend's new girlfriend,"},{"time":545802,"text":"and I have to confess when I heard this,"},{"time":549443,"text":"I just reacted with admiration."},{"time":551355,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":552932,"text":"Because, I mean, let's be real."},{"time":555347,"text":"What immense, if misplaced, creativity. Right?"},{"time":559664,"text":"This is something from a novel."},{"time":562084,"text":"This is something from a Patricia Highsmith novel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565485,"text":"Now Highsmith is a particular favorite of mine."},{"time":567655,"text":"She is the very brilliant and bizarre woman of American letters."},{"time":571707,"text":"She's the author of \"Strangers on a Train\""},{"time":573900,"text":"and \"The Talented Mr. Ripley,\""},{"time":575948,"text":"books that are all about how jealousy,"},{"time":579013,"text":"it muddles our minds,"},{"time":580888,"text":"and once we're in the sphere, in that realm of jealousy,"},{"time":583882,"text":"the membrane between what is and what could be"},{"time":589145,"text":"can be pierced in an instant."},{"time":592038,"text":"Take Tom Ripley, her most famous character."},{"time":594486,"text":"Now, Tom Ripley goes from wanting you"},{"time":597325,"text":"or wanting what you have"},{"time":599501,"text":"to being you and having what you once had,"},{"time":602929,"text":"and you're under the floorboards,"},{"time":604462,"text":"he's answering to your name,"},{"time":605825,"text":"he's wearing your rings,"},{"time":607517,"text":"emptying your bank account."},{"time":609518,"text":"That's one way to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611493,"text":"But what do we do? We can't go the Tom Ripley route."},{"time":615157,"text":"I can't give the world D's,"},{"time":617194,"text":"as much as I would really like to, some days."},{"time":620041,"text":"And it's a pity, because we live in envious times."},{"time":623539,"text":"We live in jealous times."},{"time":626446,"text":"I mean, we're all good citizens of social media,"},{"time":628459,"text":"aren't we, where the currency is envy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631843,"text":"Does the novel show us a way out? I'm not sure."},{"time":636312,"text":"So let's do what characters always do when they're not sure,"},{"time":639753,"text":"when they are in possession of a mystery."},{"time":641929,"text":"Let's go to 221B Baker Street"},{"time":644203,"text":"and ask for Sherlock Holmes."},{"time":646221,"text":"When people think of Holmes,"},{"time":648690,"text":"they think of his nemesis being Professor Moriarty,"},{"time":651799,"text":"right, this criminal mastermind."},{"time":654006,"text":"But I've always preferred [Inspector] Lestrade,"},{"time":656469,"text":"who is the rat-faced head of Scotland Yard"},{"time":659374,"text":"who needs Holmes desperately,"},{"time":661104,"text":"needs Holmes' genius, but resents him."},{"time":663408,"text":"Oh, it's so familiar to me."},{"time":665265,"text":"So Lestrade needs his help, resents him,"},{"time":669282,"text":"and sort of seethes with bitterness over the course of the mysteries."},{"time":672593,"text":"But as they work together, something starts to change,"},{"time":676470,"text":"and finally in \"The Adventure of the Six Napoleons,\""},{"time":679513,"text":"once Holmes comes in, dazzles everybody with his solution,"},{"time":683443,"text":"Lestrade turns to Holmes and he says,"},{"time":686884,"text":"\"We're not jealous of you, Mr. Holmes."},{"time":691165,"text":"We're proud of you.\""},{"time":694524,"text":"And he says that there's not a man at Scotland Yard"},{"time":696853,"text":"who wouldn't want to shake Sherlock Holmes' hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699852,"text":"It's one of the few times we see Holmes moved"},{"time":702237,"text":"in the mysteries, and I find it very moving,"},{"time":704332,"text":"this little scene, but it's also mysterious, right?"},{"time":707396,"text":"It seems to treat jealousy"},{"time":709309,"text":"as a problem of geometry, not emotion."},{"time":712047,"text":"You know, one minute Holmes is on the other side from Lestrade."},{"time":714913,"text":"The next minute they're on the same side."},{"time":716836,"text":"Suddenly, Lestrade is letting himself"},{"time":718983,"text":"admire this mind that he's resented."},{"time":721950,"text":"Could it be so simple though?"},{"time":723879,"text":"What if jealousy really is a matter of geometry,"},{"time":726310,"text":"just a matter of where we allow ourselves to stand"},{"time":730020,"text":"in relation to another?"},{"time":732350,"text":"Well, maybe then we wouldn't have to resent"},{"time":734221,"text":"somebody's excellence."},{"time":736282,"text":"We could align ourselves with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739656,"text":"But I like contingency plans."},{"time":741912,"text":"So while we wait for that to happen,"},{"time":744248,"text":"let us remember that we have fiction for consolation."},{"time":746944,"text":"Fiction alone demystifies jealousy."},{"time":749395,"text":"Fiction alone domesticates it,"},{"time":751478,"text":"invites it to the table."},{"time":753356,"text":"And look who it gathers:"},{"time":755229,"text":"sweet Lestrade, terrifying Tom Ripley,"},{"time":759065,"text":"crazy Swann, Marcel Proust himself."},{"time":763534,"text":"We are in excellent company."},{"time":765948,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":767368,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}